40f50-2 | 2026-06-13T21:36:47Z | session:40f50066fa357afb7e9e270beda982042834ee1c693a6b4dc3282abc07aeb628 | **But re-importing won't fix a query mismatch.** The discrepancy you're seeing is likely because the app and the Apple Health "Steps" screen query HealthKit differently: \n  \n The app uses `HKStatisticsCollectionQuery` with `.cumulativeSum` (`ActivityHealthKit.swift:154`), which **sums all data sources** (iPhone, Apple Watch, third-party apps). The Apple Health "Steps" view, however, uses a **preferred source priority** — it typically shows steps from one source (e.g., Apple Watch if you have one, otherwise iPhone) to avoid double-counting. \n  \n If you have an Apple Watch AND the iPhone both recording steps, the HealthKit query in the app may be combining them (resulting in higher numbers than what Health shows), or there could be gaps in one source.
